        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Add custom image provider plugin",
        "body": "## Summary\n- add a bundled `custom-image-providers` extension that exposes selected `models.providers.<id>` entries as OpenAI-compatible image-generation providers\n- support provider-specific image API key overrides at the plugin config layer\n- document the current manifest/provider-id discovery limitation for deployers\n\n## Why\nOpenClaw can already define custom chat/model providers under `models.providers`, but image generation still depends on registered capability providers. This plugin bridges that gap for OpenAI-compatible image endpoints without patching core runtime code.\n\n## Notes\n- current manifest-declared provider ids are `requesty`, `pinai`, and `muskai`\n- adding other provider ids still requires a manifest update because capability discovery is contract-based\n\n## Validation\n- `git diff --cached --check`\n- no full repo test run completed in this environment",
